			<div class="comment-body"><p>Very interesting points here, though I would add that attempting to correlate promotion decisions to actual performance is currently impossible in the Foreign Service, as the only measure of actual performance is the same EER on which promotion decisions are currently made.  It always shocked me that the FS made zero attempt to quantify actual performance, even during entry level (pre-tenure) periods.  That structural deficiencies in people management are baked into the FS was the primary motivation behind my decision to resign last year and embark on an academic career, focused on research into &#8211; surprise &#8211; how organizations can identify and develop managerial talent better.  Thank you for the excellent analysis.</p>
</div>

